Class UserData

  • java.lang.Object
    • softwareone.c482.UserData
  • public class UserData
extends java.lang.Object
    UserData is used to pass data as an object between forms and manage state across program execution.

    • Constructor Detail

      • UserData

        public UserData()
        Initializes the user data class with default data. Contains mostly immutable data after creation.

      • UserData

        public UserData​(boolean isModifying,
                boolean isPart,
                int partOrProductIndex,
                javafx.stage.Stage stageReference)
        Initializes the user data class with fully specified data.
        Parameters:
        isModifying - True if modifying a part or product, false if not.
        isPart - True if modifying a part, false if for a product.
        partOrProductIndex - 0 or higher array index of the part or product we are going to modify.
        stageReference - Reference to the newly created stage so that it can perform any necessary operations on itself.

      • UserData

        public UserData​(javafx.stage.Stage stageReference)
        Initializes the user data class with just a stage reference. Preferred use is for part or product addition actions.
